KW  - Tax rationality
KW  - Ex-day price behavior
KW  - Dividend yield
KW  - Personal taxes
KW  - Imputation tax system
AB  - Recently in this journal, it is contended that the empirically observed relationship between stock returns and dividend yields cannot be reconciled with tax rationality. In response, this present note re-examines the theoretical basis for this conclusion. We conclude that the empirical evidence of market behavior may at present be interpreted as consistent with investor tax-based rationality that capitalizes the firm's earnings on an after-personal tax basis.
